1094   Of his returne: he answered, doe not so,
1095   Slubber not businesse for my sake {Bassanio},
1096   But stay the very riping of the time,
1097   And for the {Iewes} bond which he hath of me,
1098   Let it not enter in your minde of loue:
1099   Be merry, and imploy your chiefest thoughts
1100   To courtship, and such faire ostents of loue
1101   As shall conueniently become you there;
1102   And euen there his eye being big with teares,
1103   Turning his face, he put his hand behinde him,
1104   And with affection wondrous sencible
