2569   <S {Gra}.> About a hoope of Gold, a paltry Ring
2570   That she did giue me, whose Poesie was
2571   For all the world like Cutlers Poetry
2572   Vpon a knife; {Loue mee, and leaue mee not}.
2573   <S {Ner}.> What talke you of the Poesie or the valew:
2574   You swore to me when I did giue it you,
2575   That you would weare it til the houre of death,
2576   And that it should lye with you in your graue,
2577   Though not for me, yet for your vehement oaths,
2578   You should haue beene respectiue and haue kept it.
2579   Gaue it a Iudges Clearke: but wel I know
2580   The Clearke wil nere weare haire on's face that had it.
