2591   And so riueted with faith vnto your flesh.
2592   I gaue my Loue a Ring, and made him sweare
2593   Neuer to part with it, and heere he stands:
2594   I dare be sworne for him, he would not leaue it,
2595   Nor plucke it from his finger, for the wealth
